This is an amazing app for use during virtual therapy sessions with a therapist! ... This app allows me to continue to use EMDR in my therapy sessions, during virtual sessions from home, due to the pandemic. ... I really enjoy the self-led functions for practice and reinforcement of anxiety-relieving behaviors, even when I am not overly stressed, as regular practice ingrains the behaviors so they become automatic in times of duress. ... I was quite relieved at the clear avoidance of faith/ideals or other topics besides simply healing from anxiety, in the sessions. Many other relaxation/calming apps speak of specific body parts (anxiety for an amputee), use religious wording (a trigger for those abused by "the faithful"), or visualization guidance that may contain phobias.This was what led me to believe that there were careful, thoughtful, conscientious mental health professionals involved in the creation of this healing tool. ... I told my therapist about this after I evaluated it's functions, and he is very excited to review it himself from a more clinical standpoint, with the intention of possibly suggesting it to his other virtual patients! ... To suggest an improvement; I would like to see a stereoscopic add-on for this app, as it would allow for distraction-free immersive VR functionality with even the most basic of headsets such as Google Cardboard, a huge boon for those of us with high distractability. I would accept this add-on as a micro-transaction within the app. I would suggest another improvement as well, buy my ideas have tangible value. ... ("..." Added to signify between paragraphs, as the review form turned my review into a difficult-to-read wall of text.

Amazing app but please, please, get rid of or at least lower that guitar that comes on at the end of each session. Skeptical Until I Tried It... This app has helped me get over panic attacks (and anxiety attacks) in the moment they begin. It takes practice and patience but it worked for me. We're all different, but as it's free, it's worth a shot. The first time I used this I was anxiety riddled on a plane and it got me through.

I can't say enough positive things about this app! The bilateral tapping, along with the author's calm guiding voice, quickly and thoroughly ease my stress and anxiety levels even when they're through the roof! It's like a miracle. It works 100x better than anything else I've tried, including guided meditations, sound therapy, ambient music, hypnosis, etc. Deep thanks to Mr Grant

Remarkable. I didn't expect much of this app prior to download, but I'm glad I was mistaken. My baseline anxiety has gone from a 6 (often higher) to a 3 (often lower) on a scale of 0 to 10 in the course of a few weeks. After each session I can expect a reduction of 1 or 2 points. I have even been able to record a current anxiety point of 1. I didn't think such a thing possible! Looking forward to how this app will effect my anxiety level in the months to come. Optimistic and grateful!

replyContent: Although eye movements are the most well-known form of bilateral stimulation, the audio bls has the same effect for most people (focused attention, decreased arousal) and you can do it with your eyes closed!
